						               													<description>The little fiend Prad&amp;uuml;n came from the Other Side to throw the house into confusion. Help your Family to defeat the diabolic forces that are threatening its quiet life.&amp;#10;But be careful, the enemy hides inside the walls!&amp;#10;There are four card types: Family characters (green), Objectives (white), Demons (red) and Power-ups (blue).&amp;#10;The 72 cards deck features two games in one:&amp;#10;- War at home: for 3-6 players, the complete game&amp;#10;- Run for the Prad&amp;uuml;n: a basic version using only 46 cards, for 2-4 players&amp;#10;Each player takes the role of a character (one of the family members), possessing a special ability (for example increase power of her/himself or of a fellow family member). However, one of the players is secretly possessed by the Prad&amp;uuml;n demon: his goal is to score points without being caught while the other players must find out who is it.&amp;#10;On her turn, a player can decide to attack one of the Demons and if she succeeds (having cards that grant a power greater than that of the Demon) she collects the Demon as a Victory Point (VP). During the fight, other players can help or interfere by playing additional cards. Alternatively, the player can draw additional cards to strenghten her hand.&amp;#10;VP can be spent to attack another player, hoping to reveal its objective card: if it is the Prad&amp;uuml;n, the player wins; if not, the game continues. However, if the Prad&amp;uuml;n scores 2VP, the player controlling it wins the game.&amp;#10;The game is very funny, with Demons like the &amp;quot;Damned alarm clock&amp;quot; (whose power is equal to the time of the day, in hours) or the &amp;quot;Were-elevator&amp;quot; which tries to crush and block you.&amp;#10;Power-ups can be temporary or permanent and they include things like &amp;quot;Bunny's kiss&amp;quot;, the &amp;quot;Garbage sack&amp;quot; or the &amp;quot;No-purpose knife&amp;quot;...&amp;#10;In the simplified version, character's special abilities are neglected and the family members simply race through the house fighting demons to be the first to beat the Prad&amp;uuml;n; however, other players can also be attacked and slowed down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
